01/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- At a meeting of the Balkan Political Club in Athens on Saturday (30 November), Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano urged authorities in Kosovo and Belgrade to enhance dialogue.
Nano recommended that all countries in the region, Yugoslavia in particular, promote policies of multicultural and ethnic tolerance as a prerequisite for successful integration in NATO and the EU.
The Balkan Political Club includes politicians, leaders of NGO's, prominent researchers and scholars from the region who try to offer solutions to regional problems and defend common goals.
(ATA - 30/11/02)
